'''Armoire Officielle ''' is a fashion house based out of [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]]. It has the menswear brand '''Armoire d'homme''' and the womenswear brand '''Armoire de femme'''.
==History== The company was founded as a [[menswear]] brand in 2012 by Norwegian-born designer Kjetil Aas under the name Armoire d'homme. It changed its name to Armoire Officielle when launching its first [[womenswear]] collection under the name Armoire de femme in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soundvenue.com/mode/2015/03/hold-oeje-med-det-nye-danske-maerke-armoire-de-femme-138103|title=Hold øje med: Det nye danske mærke Armoire de femme|language=Danish|publisher=Soundvenue|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref> The brand opened a flagship store at ]]Store Kannikestræde|Lille Kanikkestræde]] (No. 3) in Copenahgen in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashionforum.dk/2016/07/28/armoire-officielle-aabner-deres-foerste-butik/|title=Armoire Officielle åbner deres første butik|language=Danish|publisher=Fashion Forum|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>
