'''Dolia''' is a Catholic [[titular see]] in [[Sardinia]], [[Italy]], instituted in 1969. The diocese with see at Dolia, now [[Dolianova]], in [[Sardinia]] was suppressed in 1503, its territory going to the [[diocese of Cagliari]].<ref>[http://www.katolsk.no/utenriks/kronologi/italy.htm Chronology of Catholic Dioceses: Italy<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
It was set up around the year 1100; the date 1112 is given, but [[Benedict of Cagliari|Benedetto of Dolia]] was bishop from around 1095,<ref>http://www.santiebeati.it/dettaglio/91414, in Italian.</ref> and 1112 is the year of his death. The earlier date 1089, for bishop Virgilio, is attested.<ref>http://www.comune.selegas.ca.it/cultura.htm, in Italian.</ref>
The current bishop is [[Friedrich Ostermann]].
