{{hatnote|Not to be confused with [[Jesus is Lord Church]].}} {{Infobox religious building | building_name = Jesus is Lord Ministries | infobox_width = | image = | image_size = | caption = | location = [[Freetown]], [[Sierra Leone]] | geo = | religious_affiliation = [[Christianity]] | leadership = [[Sister]] [[Dora Dumbuya]], senior pastor | website = http://www.jesusislordministries-sl.org/ | architecture = yes | architect = | architecture_type = [[Church (building)|Church]] | architecture_style = | general_contractor = | facade_direction = | groundbreaking = | year_completed = 1989 | construction_cost = | specifications = | capacity = | length = | width = | width_nave = | height_max = | dome_quantity = | dome_height_outer = | dome_height_inner = | dome_dia_outer = | dome_dia_inner = | minaret_quantity = | minaret_height = | materials = }}
'''Jesus is Lord Ministries''' is a large [[Evangelicalism|Evangelist]] [[Local church|church]] located in the neighbourhood of [[Tower Hill (Sierra Leone)|Tower Hill]] in central [[Freetown]], the capital of Sierra Leone. The church is within close proximity to the [[Sierra Leone House of Parliament]].
The church was founded by the [[Evangelism|evangelist]] [[Christian]] [[preacher]] Sister [[Dora Dumbuya]] in 1989, who is still the senior [[pastor]] of the church.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pages.123-reg.co.uk/hsydique-1197145/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140226162426/http://pages.123-reg.co.uk/hsydique-1197145/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2014-02-26 |title=Jesus is Lord Ministries |publisher=Pages.123-reg.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-03-14 }}</ref> The church has thousands of followers, and the [[church service]] is broadcast by several radio stations across Sierra Leone.
