The '''World Bank Building''' of [[Asmara]], [[Eritrea]] is a large Italian villa built in 1938 which was bought by the [[World Bank]] to house its headquarters in that country. The architecture of the building is a mixture of [[Futurist architecture|futurist]] and [[art deco]] architectural styles.
